\begin_layout Standard
4.
 Tolerance decreases as selectivity of a IT neuron increases.
 [Zoccolan, 2007]
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
placement H
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\noindent
\align center
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename SelectivtyVsTolerence.png
	scale 50

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\size footnotesize
Tolerance vs Selectivity.
 Object selectivity and tolerance were negatively correlated across the
 anterior IT population.
 Inhibitory neurons (open circles) had a marked tendency to be both less
 shape selective than excitatory neurons (lower sparseness and morph tuning
 values) and more tolerant to identity preserving image transformations.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

