\begin_layout Standard
9.
 Receptive fields of IT neurons are dynamic.
 In plain background 39
\begin_inset Formula $\textdegree$
\end_inset

 to only 9
\begin_inset Formula $\textdegree$
\end_inset

 in complex backgrounds [Rolls 2003].
 In complex scenes, LIP area of the dorsal stream extracts salient points
 in the image and directs saccades to them.
 The ventral stream then restricts its invariant object detection to local
 area around the fovea.
 This lowers object detection requirements of IT.
 [Rolls, 2014]
\end_layout

